.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-4-6::.
House: victorian, cottage, cape-cod, colonial
4 different games are played: monopoly, whist, billiard, snooker
4 different pets are kept: goldfish, snake, hamster, guinea-pig
There are 4 different nationalities: canadian, colombian, german, indian
 1. the person playing billiard is on the left of the victorian house##1
 2. the victorian house is on the left or right of the cottage house##3
 3. the person playing monopoly is on the right of the person playing whist##1
 4. the cape-cod house is on the left or right of the cottage house##3
 5. the victorian house is in an odd position##4
 6. the owner of the guinea-pig is between the german and the owner of the snake##2
 7. the owner of the hamster is the person playing billiard##1
 8. the cottage house is the person playing billiard##1
 9. the colombian is on the far right##1
10. the canadian is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |     3     |     4     |
| House      | cape-cod  | cottage    | victorian       | colonial       |
| Game          | snooker    | billiard | whist | monopoly     |
| Pet   | goldfish | hamster        | guinea-pig    | snake   |
| Nationality   | canadian  | german      | indian    | colombian |

